FAIL-FAST PATTERNS (PREFER THESE)
When proposing killer tests, prefer (when applicable):

1) Hand-code micro-tests instead of building a new compiler/toolchain.
2) Use C/C++ intrinsics or inline ASM to access new ISA extensions quickly.
3) FPGA prototyping in a minimal/clever way to estimate circuit-level characteristics (timing/throughput/area proxies).
4) Minimalistic simulation models that capture only the critical aspects needed to test the hypothesis.
   (Avoid full-system simulations unless absolutely required.)

DEFINITIONS
- “Idea Card” = compact spec for an idea with: hypothesis, novelty claim, assumptions, failure modes,
  a cheapest decisive test, and explicit stop/pivot rules.
- “Cheapest decisive test” = smallest experiment/analysis that can strongly falsify the idea or justify a pivot.
- “Novelty claim” = what is new, relative to named baselines and prior work categories.

